The paper focuses on cybersecurity games and their effectiveness in active learning, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computer Science - Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the challenges related to designing pretests for cybersecurity games, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graph theory (cs.GR) in terms of embedding the pretest in the game. Additionally, the paper deals with cybersecurity and risk management (cs.CR) and statistical learning (cs.LG) in terms of predicting game performance through linear regression analysis.
